  "meta": {
    "title": "The Logic of Mass Expressions",
    "description": "In many languages, like English, nominal expressions headed by common nouns can be divided into two subtypes, mass expressions (like wine , silverware , wisdom ) and count expressions (like cat , army , idea ). We first characterize what mass expressions are. Then we discuss various proposals concerning their semantics.",
